        {
            "_id": "MgZI2Tz1Jw2Zi1T8",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.UMAXLDpI6YLSfYX1"
            },
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/alchemical-items/drugs/alcohol.webp",
            "name": "Bottle of Wine",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "baseItem": null,
                "bulk": {
                    "value": 0.1
                },
                "category": "drug",
                "containerId": null,
                "damage": null,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Alcohol is a common substance available in stunning variety. The Price of a dose of alcohol depends on the specific beverage. You can't recover from the sickened condition from alcohol while affected.</p>\n<p>If you fail a saving throw against alcohol other than initial saves, the affliction's stage doesn't increase; the only way to increase the stage of alcohol's affliction is to consume more alcohol.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">A</span> Interact (Ingested)</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[fortitude|dc:12]</p>\n<p><strong>Onset</strong> 10 minutes</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> +1 item bonus to saving throws against fear (10 minutes)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard], +1 item bonus to saving throws against fear effects (10 minutes)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1}, off-guard, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} (10 minutes)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} (10 minutes)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> clumsy 2, sickened 2, and stupefied 2 (10 minutes)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 6</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Unconscious] (8 hours)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 7</strong> death</p>"
                },
